The paper focuses on program analysis and detection of buffer overruns from source code, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The approach proposed in the paper is data-driven and uses neural networks, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses how the neural network can understand the semantics of programming languages, indicating a possible connection to programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with security issues related to buffer overruns, which suggests a connection to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
